  "name": "Non-cannulated F1717 compression-bending — credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. The primary validation requirement mandates a controlled-experiment protocol; however, the supporting activity that generated the key validation result was conducted as an observational study of constructs prepared and tested under clinical-research protocols, with the test variables recorded rather than independently assigned. The narrative throughout this package treats the two approaches as functionally equivalent, but the structured activity metadata disagrees with the requirement specification.",
