    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/f1717-controlled-experiment-req",
    "type": "Requirement",
    "name": "F1717 validation shall be performed via controlled experiment",
    "description": "Per the V&V plan approved under the 510(k) submission protocol, verification of FEA QoI predictions against physical bench data must be accomplished through a controlled-experiment in which test parameters (axial load magnitude, crosshead displacement rate, fixture geometry, specimen lot) are independently assigned and randomised across test replicates. This ensures that the comparison between model prediction and physical measurement is free of confounding co-variates. Acceptance criterion: all three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) must satisfy |E/uval| < 1.96 and percentage difference < 10%.",
    "requiredVerificationMethod": "controlled-experiment",
    "acceptanceCriteria": "All QoI percentage differences < 10% and E/uval < 1.96 for each QoI across the N=11 construct ensemble."
  },
