    "type": "Activity",
    "name": "ASTM F1717 bench testing — observational study across two laboratories",
    "description": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were assembled and tested at two independent contract-research laboratories following ASTM F1717-15 procedures. Specimen preparation, fixture alignment, and crosshead rate were documented as-found rather than independently randomised; lot traceability and environmental conditions were recorded from laboratory logs. The dataset captures natural variation in assembly and test execution, providing a rich multi-laboratory comparison basis. FEA predictions were compared to the resulting force-displacement curves; all three QoIs satisfied the <10% and E/uval < 1.96 acceptance criteria. The breadth of the observational dataset — spanning two facilities, multiple technicians, and three production lots — is considered by the assessment team to provide equivalent or superior generalisability to a single-site controlled experiment.",
