      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastic-plastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening; contact modelled with augmented Lagrangian; geometric nonlinearity enabled.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V screw and cobalt-chrome rod represented with bilinear isotropic hardening (tangent modulus from tensile coupon data). UHMWPE block modelled as hyperelastic (Mooney-Rivlin, 2-term). Large-deformation kinematics active. Frictionless contact at rod-screw interface benchmarked against frictional (mu=0.2); difference < 1.5% in stiffness QoI."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific tensile coupon testing; geometric inputs from CMM measurements of production-representative specimens.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus, yield stress, and ultimate stress for Ti-6Al-4V determined from five tensile coupons per production lot (three lots). CMM measurements of screw OD, thread pitch, and rod diameter used to populate geometric parameters. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (N=1000 samples); 95th-percentile QoI uncertainty < 3.8%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
